organic_results.title: Postsecondary education of white women in 1900
organic_results.snippet: This article uses state-level data from 1900 to examine relationships between social-structural characteristics and enrollments in three types of institutions of higher education: coeducational colleges and universities, women's colleges, and normal schools. Historically, higher education served diverse functions for women and society, including occupational preparation, training in domestic and social skills, status maintenance, and warehousing of idle populations. The three types of institutions differed in their fulfillment of these functions …
